Karachi bourse closed Sunday due to member ' s death . The Karachi Stock Exchange ( KSE ) will remain closed on Sunday because of the death of one of its members , an exchange official said on Saturday . He said the KSE , which closed for the Friday - Saturday weekend , would reopen on Monday . KSE ' s 100 share price index closed 3 . 15 points , or 0 . 23 percent , higher on the last trading session on Tuesday amid 146 losers and 97 gainers in a turnover of 24 million shares , up from Monday ' s 22 million . - - Karachi newsroom 9221 - 5685192 
